<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ901231-0044</DOCNO><DOCID>901231-0044.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- American Recreation Centers Inc.:   Purchase of 400,000 Shares   By ESOP Cleared by Board</HL><DATE>12/31/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AMRC LABOR</CO><IN>RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)</IN><LP>   American Recreation Centers Inc. said its board authorizedthe purchase of 400,000 shares by its Employee StockOwnership Plan.   The transaction was financed by a loan to the employeeorganization from the company and will be repaid over fiveyears from annual contributions made to the organization bythe company. The company said it used its credit line tosecure the loan.</LP><TEXT>   The Sacramento, Calif., company said it purchases stockfor its members from time to time on the open market andadded that it will continue to do so.   American Recreation Centers owns 22 bowling centers inCalifornia and five in Texas. It also owns Right StartCatalog Inc., a direct marketer of products for infants andchildren.</TEXT></DOC>